# How to install android sdk on ubuntu

1. Go to developer.android.com to find how to download android-sdk-linux.tgz
2. Extract the archive
3. Move it to /opt/
4. Read the SDK Readme.txt
5. Update sdk in command line, can find the command line in the SDK Readme.txt
	tools/android update sdk --no-ui
	It takes time to finish all of the updates

	If you don't want to let it updates too many things, you can run sdk manager and 
	install what you want, just run
		tools/android

	To run avd manager
		tools/android avd

